08138nam a22010695i 9783035616538DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20182018sz     fo  d z      eng d  a97830356165387 a10.1515/97830356165382doi  a(DE-B1597)494342  a(OCoLC)1054881589  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 7aARC0050002bisacsh0483ua728.820943309034qDE-101223/ger04aThe Architecture under King Ludwig II – Palaces and Factories /ced. by Andres Lepik, Katrin Bäumler. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2018] 4c©2018  a1 online resource (320 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tGreeting by Ernst von Siemens Kunststiftung -- tPreface -- tINTRODUCTION -- tESSAYS -- tLudwig II: On the Legacy of an Artist on the Throne -- tArchitecture as the Availability of History? Reflections on a New Understanding of the Buildings of King Ludwig II of Bavaria -- tSacredness in the Buildings of Ludwig II -- tPresent in the Past: Ludwig II and Architecture Photography 1864–86 -- tKing Ludwig II’s View of the World -- tExotic Conceptions of Space? Sources and Variations in Ludwig’s Perception of Islamic Architecture -- tMediated Architectural (Dream) Spaces: Ludwig II and the Middle Ages “at Third Hand” -- tEngineering the “Fairy Tale”: Infrastructure under Ludwig II -- tMunicipal Authority and Aesthetic Dignity. The Competition for the Munich City Hall -- tThe Aestheticization of Technology in Historicism: The Neue Polytechnische Schule in Munich -- tWorkers’ Housing at the Time of Ludwig II -- tThe Kunstverein Building by Eduard von Riedel: A first Project of Ludwig II in Munich -- tBUILDING TYPES -- tI Urban Planning -- tII Transportation -- tIII Industry, Trade, and Commerce -- tIV Health, Hygiene, and Social Welfare -- tV Education and Schooling -- tVI Housing -- tVII Culture and Entertainment -- tVIII Industrial Exhibitions -- tIX Government and Municipal Administration -- tX Military -- tXI Churches and Synagogues -- tXII Palaces and Castles -- tBIBLIOGRAPHY -- tPHOTO CREDITS -- tTHANKS0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aLudwig II of Bavaria (1864—1886) is more internationally known for his royal palaces than hardly any other regent of the 19th century. They are the symbol of a personal architectural vision which, to this day, fascinates people from all over the world. However, the fame of his palaces has eclipsed other construction activities in the Kingdom of Bavaria: urban developments, hospitals, and schools, theatres and museums, but also factories, railway stations, apartment blocks, churches, and synagogues were created under his regency. This book, for the first time, sheds light on the broad architectural activities in this epoch. Essays and overview illustrations of the building projects of the time provide insights into the diversity of the then building culture and, at the same time, open up a new perspective on the royal palaces.  aLudwig II. von Bayern (1864–1886) ist durch seine Königsschlösser international so bekannt wie kaum ein anderer Regent des 19. Jahrhunderts. Sie sind das Symbol einer persönlichen Architekturvision, die bis heute ein Publikum aus aller Welt fasziniert. Der Ruhm seiner Schlösser hat den Blick auf die andere Bautätigkeit im Königreich Bayern jedoch überstrahlt: Städtebau, Krankenhäuser, Schulbauten, Theater und Museen, aber auch Fabriken, Bahnhöfe, Mietshäuser, Kirchen und Synagogen entstanden unter seiner Regentschaft. Das Buch beleuchtet erstmals das breite Architekturgeschehen dieser Epoche. Essays und Überblicksdarstellungen zu den Bauaufgaben der damaligen Zeit geben Einblicke in die Vielfalt der Baukultur und rücken die Königsschlösser zugleich in eine neue Perspektive.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (pub